    <p><strong>Welcome to the Launch Pad of New Technology – the 2010 International CES!</strong><br> 
by Howie Cooperstein</p>
    <p>I would like to take this opportunity to tell you about the <A href="/exhibitors/resources/advisoryBoard.asp" target=_blank>CES Exhibitor Advisory Board (EAB)</A> and how we work for you and all CES exhibitors. The EAB formally introduced itself to you at the 2007 International CES, though we’ve been in existence for a number of years. As CES exhibitors ourselves, we serve on behalf of all exhibiting companies, working collectively with the CES organization on everything from housing to transportation, labor to policy changes, and many other aspects of the show.&nbsp;We have found it very beneficial for a representative board such as ours to provide feedback to CES, optimizing the CES exhibiting experience for all exhibitors. We are eager to speak with you to learn of not only your successes at CES, but any issues you face in your exhibiting experience as well. It’s only when topics are brought to the table and discussed that problems can be solved and things that are already good can be improved upon.<BR><BR>We encourage you to contact us at any time of the year (on-site at CES or via e-mail, phone, etc.) to not only keep us informed as your representatives, but also to learn more about the CES Exhibitor Advisory Board and how you might also serve sometime in the future. We are eager to offer guidance and help.<BR><BR>The board meets quarterly to address matters on a fairly prompt schedule. Sometimes answers are not immediate, but we have realized a great track record in continual improvements to the show.<BR><BR>Our contact information is on <A href="/exhibitors/resources/advisoryBoard.asp" target=_blank>CESweb.org/EAB</A> and we look forward to hearing from you! We wish you a happy, healthy and prosperous New Year and a wonderfully successful 2010 International CES!&nbsp; <BR><BR>Kind regards,<BR><BR><IMG src="/docs/HA_Sig.jpg"><BR>Howie Cooperstein<BR>Chair, International CES Exhibitor Advisory Board<BR></p>
