<a name="3617"></a>

<div class="sub-content-header">Space Selection Packets Coming Soon – Via E-mail</div>
<br />

<IMG hspace=5 align=right src="/images/content/2011logo.jpg" width=165 height=94>On-site 2011 International CES space selection information will be sent to current exhibitors via e-mail.&nbsp; Please look for this important information the week of December 14. This e-mail will include your scheduled space selection date, time and space selection number as well as web links to other space selection information such as floor plans. Hospitality suites and high-performance audio space selection will take place after the 2010 show.<BR><BR>As a current CES exhibitor, you already know why tradeshows are an important investment for your company. Here are a few stats that we have collected that remind all of us why tradeshows are worth your time and money: 
<UL class=text>
<LI class=text>55% of attendees plan to buy one or more products/services exhibited at the tradeshow within 12 months after the event. (Source: Exhibit Surveys, Inc. and Advertising Research Foundation, 2008) </LI>
<LI class=text>$215—the cost to close a sale from trade show lead vs.$1,039—the cost to close a sales without a tradeshow lead. Meeting a customer at a tradeshow saves the exhibitor $824. (Source: The Cost Effectiveness of Exhibition Participation: Part II, CEIR 2009) </LI>
<LI class=text>45% of attendees develop an emotional connection with a brand after interacting with it at a tradeshow. (Source: Exhibit Surveys, Inc. 2007) </LI>
<LI class=text>91% of business decision-makers agree that it’s easier to recognize or remember a company’s brand or products/services when they see messages about it in multiple media sources such as magazines, online, and events. (Source: American Business Media/ Forrester Research 2008)</LI></UL>
        <br /><img width="1" height="20" src="/images/framework/spacer.gif"/>
        <img height="15" alt="" src="/images/framework/divider-line.gif"/><br />

<a name="3616"></a>

<div class="sub-content-header">Exhibitor Staff Guides Now Available</div>
<br />

Are you putting together a 2010 International CES on-site staff guide for your company?&nbsp; If so, we just made it a lot easier for you to create a guide for your colleagues to use on-site. <A href="/exhibitors/newsletter/exhibitorStaff.asp">Please visit our website </A>to choose from an array of helpful documents – from badge holder pickup information to a list of suggested restaurants. You may want to include a personalized cover, your booth number and company contact information. Otherwise, we have taken care of the rest for you!
        <br /><img width="1" height="20" src="/images/framework/spacer.gif"/>
        <img height="15" alt="" src="/images/framework/divider-line.gif"/><br />

<a name="3615"></a>

<div class="sub-content-header">A New Addition to Your Social Media Circle </div>
<br />

<IMG hspace=5 align=right src="/images/content/socialcirclelogo.jpg" width=200 height=128>Expand your social circle at the world's largest and coolest display of consumer technology. Keep on top of the global conversation buzzing about you, your competitors and the brightest stars of 2010.&nbsp;Visit the CES Social Circle, a powerful social networking aggregator, beginning in December to catch the momentum unveiled around tech's must-see and must-have new hits. The site, created in partnership with <A href="http://jess3.com/" target=_blank>Jess3</A>, will analyze trends from Twitter, YouTube, Flickr and across the blogosphere, providing real time data on the products, brands and personalities behind the annual stage for innovation. <BR><BR>If you would like your company's official Twitter account to be included, please contact <A href="mailto: jgizzi@ce.org" target=_blank>Joe Gizzi</A>. 
        <br /><img width="1" height="20" src="/images/framework/spacer.gif"/>
        <img height="15" alt="" src="/images/framework/divider-line.gif"/><br />

<a name="3614"></a>

<div class="sub-content-header">Complete 2010 CES Keynote Lineup Announced</div>
<br />

Seven influential leaders in consumer electronics (CE) will help you envision the possibilities for your business, and the year ahead, as they deliver riveting <A href="/sessions/keynotes.asp">keynote addresses at the International CES</A>. Listen as they share valuable lessons learned and discuss how their respective businesses will launch forward in the coming decade. All keynote addresses will take place in the Las Vegas Hilton. 
<UL class=text>
<LI class=text>Steve Ballmer<BR>CEO, Microsoft Corp.<BR><BR></LI>
<LI class=text>Gary Shapiro<BR>President and CEO, Consumer Electronics Association (CEA)&reg;<BR><BR></LI>
<LI class=text>Alan Mulally<BR>President and CEO, Ford Motor Co.<BR><BR></LI>
<LI class=text>Paul Otellini<BR>President and CEO, Intel Corp.<BR><BR></LI>
<LI class=text>Dr. Paul Jacobs<BR>CEO, Qualcomm<BR><BR></LI>
<LI class=text>Olli-Pekka Kallasvuo<BR>CEO, Nokia<BR><BR></LI>
<LI class=text>Zhou Houjian<BR>Chairman, Hisense Group Co. Ltd. <BR></LI></UL><A href="/sessions/keynotes.asp" target=_blank>View full keynote details</A>.<BR>
        <br /><img width="1" height="20" src="/images/framework/spacer.gif"/>
        <img height="15" alt="" src="/images/framework/divider-line.gif"/><br />

<a name="3601"></a>

<div class="sub-content-header">Celebrities at CES!</div>
<br />

Monster Cable just announced that six-time Grammy Award winner John Legend will perform at the Monster Retailer Awards/Concert at the 2010 International CES!<BR><BR>Is your company planning a special concert with a popular chart-topper, too? How about an autograph session with Hollywood royalty or a product demonstration with a sports legend? <A href="/docs/SpEventCeleb_form.pdf" target=_blank>If so, let us know!</A> We can assist you with special security arrangements, staging requirements, catering requests or anything else you need to make your event a success. <BR><BR>We’ll help you publicize it by including details on CESweb.org, in news releases and in the press room. Many exhibitors that host special events or celebrities choose not to announce their events until closer to the show and we will certainly accommodate that as well. <A href="mailto:afried@CE.org">Contact Allison Fried</A> for more information.<BR>
        <br /><img width="1" height="20" src="/images/framework/spacer.gif"/>
        <img height="15" alt="" src="/images/framework/divider-line.gif"/><br />

<a name="3600"></a>

<div class="sub-content-header">GREEN PRESS ROOM and Electronic Press Kit Preparation</div>
<br />

This year the International CES press kit area is going green! In an effort to reduce our environmental footprint and in accordance with media feedback, the LVCC press room will only house electronic exhibitor press kits. Exhibitors are welcome to bring in a one page spec sheet that lists media contacts and the URL that your electronic press kit is housed at. They can also bring in USB drives and CDs. Printed press materials greater than one page in length should be stored in the exhibitor’s booth.<BR><BR>For more press kit and exhibitor PR information, please check out our <A href="/exhibitors/newsletter/prKit.asp" target=_blank>2010 International CES Exhibitor PR Kit</A>. <BR>
        <br /><img width="1" height="20" src="/images/framework/spacer.gif"/>
        <img height="15" alt="" src="/images/framework/divider-line.gif"/><br />

<a name="3613"></a>

<div class="sub-content-header">Don’t Make Decisions About the Future of Your Business in the Dark</div>
<br />

<IMG hspace=5 align=right src="/images/content/CEA_MArketMetrics.jpg" width=200 height=36>The Consumer Electronics Association (CEA) is your trusted source for data and analysis on the consumer electronics market. CEA’s CE MarketMetrics market data program has helped companies successfully measure sales performance and plan for the future by tracking factory sales of consumer technology products through U.S consumer sales channels for more than 80 years.&nbsp; <BR><BR><STRONG>Limited time offer: Save 20% on any CE MarketMetrics data report subscription through December 31, 2009.</STRONG>&nbsp; Ask about additional discounts for report participants. For more information about the CE MarketMetrics program and to view a list of available data reports, visit <A href="http://www.cemarketmetrics.org" target=_blank>CEMarketMetrics.org</A> or contact Steve Koenig at 703-907-4317.
        <br /><img width="1" height="20" src="/images/framework/spacer.gif"/>
        <img height="15" alt="" src="/images/framework/divider-line.gif"/><br />

<a name="3599"></a>

<div class="sub-content-header">Experience Brilliant Innovation</div>
<br />

<IMG height=150 hspace=5 src="/images/content/2010_innovations.jpg" width=98 align=right><A href="/awards/innovations/default.asp">The Innovations 2010 Design and Engineering Awards program</A> recognizes brilliant consumer electronics (CE) products in the industry's hottest product categories. <A href="/awards/innovations/2010honorees.asp">This year’s Innovations Honorees</A>&nbsp;were revealed in New York at the 2010 International CES Press Preview on November 10, 2009.<BR><BR>Experience stunning products in a variety of CE categories, including brand new Innovations honors for software programs, media content and online applications. Celebrate with the honorees in New York and make sure to visit the <A href="/exhibits/displays/innovShowcase.asp">Innovations 2010 Showcase</A> during CES in the Las Vegas Convention Center, Grand Lobby.
